3/*
4 * /src/NTP/ntp4-dev/libparse/parse_conf.c,v 4.9 2005/04/16 17:32:10 kardel RELEASE_20050508_A

6 * parse_conf.c,v 4.9 2005/04/16 17:32:10 kardel RELEASE_20050508_A
7 *
8 * Parser configuration module for reference clocks
9 *
10 * STREAM define switches between two personalities of the module
11 * if STREAM is defined this module can be used with dcf77sync.c as
12 * a STREAMS kernel module. In this case the time stamps will be
13 * a struct timeval.
14 * when STREAM is not defined NTP time stamps will be used.

105/*
106 * format definitions
107 */
108clockformat_t *clockformats[] =
109{
110#ifdef CLOCK_MEINBERG
111 &clock_meinberg[0],
112 &clock_meinberg[1],
113 &clock_meinberg[2],
114#endif
115#ifdef CLOCK_DCF7000
116 &clock_dcf7000,
117#endif
118#ifdef CLOCK_SCHMID
119 &clock_schmid,
120#endif
121#ifdef CLOCK_RAWDCF
122 &clock_rawdcf,
123#endif
124#ifdef CLOCK_TRIMTAIP
125 &clock_trimtaip,
126#endif
127#ifdef CLOCK_TRIMTSIP
128 &clock_trimtsip,
129#endif
130#ifdef CLOCK_RCC8000
131 &clock_rcc8000,
132#endif
133#ifdef CLOCK_HOPF6021
134 &clock_hopf6021,
135#endif
136#ifdef CLOCK_COMPUTIME
137 &clock_computime,
138#endif
139#ifdef CLOCK_WHARTON_400A
140 &clock_wharton_400a,
141#endif
142#ifdef CLOCK_VARITEXT
143 &clock_varitext,
144#endif
145#ifdef CLOCK_SEL240X
146 &clock_sel240x,
147#endif
148 0};
149
150unsigned short nformats = sizeof(clockformats) / sizeof(clockformats[0]) - 1;
151
152#else /* not (REFCLOCK && CLOCK_PARSE) */
153int parse_conf_bs;
154#endif /* not (REFCLOCK && CLOCK_PARSE) */
